{{no footnotes|date=May 2014}} '''Léon Wieger''' (born July 9, 1856 in [[Strasbourg]], [[France]] - died March 25, 1933 in [[Xian County]], [[Hebei]], [[China]]), was a French [[Jesuit]] missionary, medical doctor, theologist and sinologist who worked at the Catholic Jesuit mission in [[Hejian]], together with [[Séraphin Couvreur]].
He has published numerous books, on Chinese culture, Taoism, Buddhism and Chinese language.
